<div id="review_1071528272" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1071528272" />
    <a title="Pamela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30071749-pamela"><img alt="Pamela" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509728263p2/30071749.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1071528272?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pamela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pamela" href="/user/show/30071749-pamela">Pamela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781854878892" href="/book/show/1862791.Catilina_s_Riddle">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30071749-pamela?shelf=crime-historical-mystery">crime-historical-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1071528272" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12270028530333330310">The third episode in the series finds Gordianus on a farm in Etruria, a legacy from a friend. He has decided to turn his back on his life of intrigue in Rome, but soon finds life in the country every bit as difficult. Faced with the enmity of his neighbours (relatives of the deceased who had hoped to inherit) and visited by contacts from his past, he finds himself being dragged back to the life he thought he had escaped.<br/><br/>Not my favourite from the series - I didn&apos;t really enjoy the farm setting an</span>
  <span id="freeText12270028530333330310" style="display:none">The third episode in the series finds Gordianus on a farm in Etruria, a legacy from a friend. He has decided to turn his back on his life of intrigue in Rome, but soon finds life in the country every bit as difficult. Faced with the enmity of his neighbours (relatives of the deceased who had hoped to inherit) and visited by contacts from his past, he finds himself being dragged back to the life he thought he had escaped.<br /><br />Not my favourite from the series - I didn't really enjoy the farm setting and the mystery set up there was a bit obvious and plodding. There was also a lot of historical information being shared through Gordianus telling his son Meto - while interesting in itself, the method of delivery was a bit stilted and forced. The times when Gordianus was back in Rome were far more interesting and lively, and the political machinations were fascinating. Gordianus is as entertaining as ever, though, and his relationships with his family give us some great moments.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12270028530333330310" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


