<span id="freeTextContainer7259364383311316827">It’s over 10 years since I read this book previously and have recently been revisiting Steven Saylor’s Gordianus series. It had me gripped all over again the second time. As a professional classicist and teacher I can be rather over critical when reading historical fiction, looking for faults, inaccuracies and anachronisms. But as with all Steven Saylor’s books his research is meticulous and attention to detail admirable. In particular, the character of Catilina is believable and skilfully craft</span>
  <span id="freeText7259364383311316827" style="display:none">It’s over 10 years since I read this book previously and have recently been revisiting Steven Saylor’s Gordianus series. It had me gripped all over again the second time. As a professional classicist and teacher I can be rather over critical when reading historical fiction, looking for faults, inaccuracies and anachronisms. But as with all Steven Saylor’s books his research is meticulous and attention to detail admirable. In particular, the character of Catilina is believable and skilfully crafted. All I can say is bring on The Venus Throw!!</span>
