<div id="review_2293300847" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2293300847" />
    <a title="Cat Sheely" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5076682-cat-sheely"><img alt="Cat Sheely" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1299629681p2/5076682.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2293300847?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cat Sheely" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cat Sheely" href="/user/show/5076682-cat-sheely">Cat Sheely</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781849016094" href="/book/show/10616389-catilina-s-riddle">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5076682-cat-sheely?shelf=historical-crime">historical-crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5076682-cat-sheely?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2293300847" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9666432121524677866">As with the previous two books in this series, Catilina&apos;s Riddle is a satisfying &apos;who done it&apos; with a great deal of Roman history that feels natural throughout. Gordianus is now much older, in his forties, and living on a farm left to him by a mentor and friend. His neighbours are not at all friendly, when he is called upon by Cicero, whom he no longer considers a friend, to spy for him. From there, things go from bad to worse.<br/><br/>The story is wrapped around the Rome of ancient times, it&apos;s customs, </span>
  <span id="freeText9666432121524677866" style="display:none">As with the previous two books in this series, Catilina's Riddle is a satisfying 'who done it' with a great deal of Roman history that feels natural throughout. Gordianus is now much older, in his forties, and living on a farm left to him by a mentor and friend. His neighbours are not at all friendly, when he is called upon by Cicero, whom he no longer considers a friend, to spy for him. From there, things go from bad to worse.<br /><br />The story is wrapped around the Rome of ancient times, it's customs, it's senate, it's politics and particularly the character of Cicero and his antipathy of Catilina. I studied Latin and Roman history but never have Cicero's speeches come as alive, or been put in such an interesting context as in this novel. <br /><br />Never is it boring, always the story is intriguing with its twists and turns yet we see and hear Cicero as if he is alive in all his haughty oratory. Love it.<br /><br />So, if you like thrillers, crime novels, history and a good yarn, this is for you.<br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="9666432121524677866" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


